---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Hours, Not Years - Be More Free">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="relative py-23 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-50 via-white to-accent-50"></div>
    
    <!-- Decorative elements -->
    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-96 h-96 bg-gradient-to-bl from-accent-200/20 to-transparent rounded-full blur-3xl"></div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-96 h-96 bg-gradient-to-tr from-primary-200/20 to-transparent rounded-full blur-3xl"></div>
    
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 relative z-10">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
        <div class="text-6xl mb-6">‚ö°</div>
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8 leading-tight">
          Hours, <span class="text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-primary-600 to-accent-500">Not Years</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-2xl text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          Stop managing symptoms with endless coping mechanisms. Address what's actually there.
        </p>
        <nav class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 transition-colors">
          <a href="/booking/free-trial" class="inline-flex items-center">
            ‚Üê Back 
          </a>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main Content -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      <!-- Core Principle -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
          Why Traditional Approaches Take So Long
        </h2>
        
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-50 to-accent-50 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-8">
          <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            Traditional therapy often operates on the assumption that change is inherently slow, 
            that you need to build a "therapeutic relationship" first, that you must work through 
            things gradually according to established protocols and frameworks.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            The Neutral Zone takes a different approach: when you have actual space to look at 
            what's there‚Äîwithout interference, interpretation, or agenda‚Äîchange can happen as 
            quickly as insight emerges.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- The Difference -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-gray-900">
          Managing vs. Resolving
        </h3>
        
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-red-50 to-orange-50 border border-red-200 rounded-xl p-6">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-red-900 flex items-center">
              <span class="text-red-500 mr-3 text-2xl">üîÑ</span>
              Traditional: Managing Symptoms
            </h4>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
              <li>‚Ä¢ Weekly sessions for months or years</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Learning coping strategies</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Managing triggers and responses</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Building skills to handle symptoms</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Gradual improvement over time</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Ongoing maintenance required</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 border border-green-200 rounded-xl p-6">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-green-900 flex items-center">
              <span class="text-green-500 mr-3 text-2xl">‚ö°</span>
              Neutral Zone: Examining What's There
            </h4>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
              <li>‚Ä¢ Direct examination of your experience</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Understanding emerges naturally</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Resolution often happens quickly</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ No ongoing management needed</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Real change, not just coping</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Insights lead to lasting shifts</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- What This Looks Like -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-gray-900">
          What "Hours, Not Years" Looks Like
        </h3>
        
        <div class="space-y-8">
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 border border-green-200 rounded-xl p-6">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4 text-green-900">
              Example: Public Speaking Anxiety
            </h4>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm font-medium text-red-700 mb-2">Traditional Approach:</p>
                <p class="text-gray-700 italic">
                  Months of exposure therapy, breathing techniques, cognitive restructuring, 
                  gradual challenges, ongoing practice...
                </p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm font-medium text-green-700 mb-2">Neutral Zone Approach:</p>
                <p class="text-gray-700 italic">
                  "Where do you suppose that public speaking anxiety began?" Direct examination 
                  often reveals the core issue in a single session.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 border border-green-200 rounded-xl p-6">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4 text-green-900">
              Example: Relationship Patterns
            </h4>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm font-medium text-red-700 mb-2">Traditional Approach:</p>
                <p class="text-gray-700 italic">
                  Years exploring attachment styles, childhood patterns, communication 
                  skills training, boundary work...
                </p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm font-medium text-green-700 mb-2">Neutral Zone Approach:</p>
                <p class="text-gray-700 italic">
                  "What happens inside you when you get close to someone?" 
                  The pattern becomes visible immediately.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 border border-green-200 rounded-xl p-6">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4 text-green-900">
              Example: Work Burnout
            </h4>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm font-medium text-red-700 mb-2">Traditional Approach:</p>
                <p class="text-gray-700 italic">
                  Stress management techniques, work-life balance strategies, 
                  self-care routines, boundary setting...
                </p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm font-medium text-green-700 mb-2">Neutral Zone Approach:</p>
                <p class="text-gray-700 italic">
                  "What bad thing might happen if you let go of all that?" Often reveals the 
                  underlying dynamic in hours.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Why This Is Possible -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-gray-900">
          Why Change Can Happen So Quickly
        </h3>
        
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 hover:border-primary-300 transition-colors">
            <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
              <span class="text-3xl">üéØ</span>
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Direct Examination</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700">
                  When you can look directly at what's actually there‚Äîwithout filtering through 
                  theories or frameworks‚Äîunderstanding often emerges immediately.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 hover:border-primary-300 transition-colors">
            <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
              <span class="text-3xl">üß†</span>
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">No Need to Build Rapport</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700">
                  You don't need months to develop trust or a "therapeutic relationship." 
                  The neutral space itself creates safety for exploration.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 hover:border-primary-300 transition-colors">
            <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
              <span class="text-3xl">üí°</span>
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Your Own Insights Are Powerful</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700">
                  When insights come from your own looking rather than someone else's 
                  interpretation, they tend to create immediate and lasting change.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 hover:border-primary-300 transition-colors">
            <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
              <span class="text-3xl">üö´</span>
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">No Resistance to Overcome</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700">
                  When no one is trying to convince you of anything, there's nothing to 
                  resist. You can examine your material freely.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Important Note -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-gray-900">
          This Doesn't Mean Magic
        </h3>
        
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-50 to-orange-50 border-2 border-amber-300 rounded-2xl p-8">
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            "Hours, not years" doesn't mean everything resolves in one session or that 
            change is effortless. It means that when you have genuine space to look at 
            what's there, progress happens at the speed of understanding.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            Some people do have significant breakthroughs in single sessions. Others need 
            several sessions to examine different aspects of their material. But the process 
            isn't designed to take years‚Äîit's designed to be as efficient as your own 
            understanding allows.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            The key difference is that you're not spending time learning someone else's 
            system or building a relationship with a professional. You're spending time 
            looking at your own material with the support of a truly neutral space.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related Principles -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-8 text-center text-gray-900">
        Other Neutral Zone Principles
      </h3>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <a href="/principles/no-altitude" class="bg-white rounded-xl p-4 border border-gray-200 hover:border-primary-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all group">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <span class="text-2xl">üéØ</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-semibold group-hover:text-primary-600 transition-colors">No One Has Altitude Over You</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">You explore what YOU want to explore</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </a>
        
        <a href="/principles/truth" class="bg-white rounded-xl p-4 border border-gray-200 hover:border-primary-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all group">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <span class="text-2xl">üíØ</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-semibold group-hover:text-primary-600 transition-colors">Everything You Say is Truth</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Your experience is valid, period</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </a>
        
        <a href="/principles/find-answers" class="bg-white rounded-xl p-4 border border-gray-200 hover:border-primary-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all group">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <span class="text-2xl">üß≠</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-semibold group-hover:text-primary-600 transition-colors">Find Your Own Answers</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Your wisdom emerges with space</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </a>
        
        <a href="/principles/complete-acceptance" class="bg-white rounded-xl p-4 border border-gray-200 hover:border-primary-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all group">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <span class="text-2xl">ü§ù</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-semibold group-hover:text-primary-600 transition-colors">Complete Acceptance</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Examine all parts without judgment</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </a>
        
        <a href="/principles/no-prerequisites" class="bg-white rounded-xl p-4 border border-gray-200 hover:border-primary-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all group">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <span class="text-2xl">üöÄ</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-semibold group-hover:text-primary-600 transition-colors">No Prerequisites</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Just start looking</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <section class="py-24 relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-600 via-primary-700 to-accent-600"></div>
    
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 text-center relative z-10">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-white mb-6">
        Ready to Experience Real Change?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-white/90 mb-10 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        Your first 30-minute Neutral Zone session is free. Discover what happens 
        when you can examine what's actually there.
      </p>
      <button 
         data-cal-link="be-more-free/30min"
         data-cal-namespace="30min"
         data-cal-config='{"layout":"month_view"}'
         class="group bg-white text-primary-700 px-12 py-6 rounded-full text-xl font-bold hover:bg-accent-400 hover:text-white transition-all duration-300 transform hover:scale-105 shadow-2xl inline-flex items-center cursor-pointer">
        Book Your Free Trial Session
        <span class="ml-3 group-hover:translate-x-2 transition-transform">‚Üí</span>
      </button>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
